(Nielen de Klerk, News24) Multimedia &nbsp; &nbsp; User Galleries &nbsp; &nbsp; News in Pictures Send us your pictures &nbsp; &nbsp; Send us your stories Johannesburg - Drugs with an estimated street value of R19.5m were seized at O R Tambo international airport in Johannesburg on Friday, the SA Revenue Service said. The drugs were concealed in hair-piece packages from Nigeria, spokesperson Marika Muller said in a statement."Those packages contained crystal methamphetamine [tik] weighing a total of 65kg, with a value of R19.5m."This is one of the biggest ever seizures of crystal methamphetamine at OR Tambo," Muller said.The drugs were handed over to the police.24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.